Roti Canai / Teh Tarik (Malacca, Malaysia)

The Indian prata is a round flat pancake that is cooked by heating over a flat grill plate. It is a popular dish in Singapore and Malaysia, and is often eaten with mutton or fish curry. Recent variations of the dish include paper or tissue prata, where the thin dough is not folded, but instead heated into a paper-like cone shape.
